<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="97" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,310,1032,1058]" box="[189,310,1032,1058]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1032,1058]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1032,1058]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[187,1399,1079,1211]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
Species belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Buckton" authorityYear="1905" box="[549,642,1080,1105]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[549,642,1080,1105]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Hamma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with thorax eminently brown, pronotum smooth and metopidium not densely tuberculate; suprahumeral horns with a laterally pointing thorn; a posterior process with four nodes, V-shaped in lateral view between the second and fourth nodes; last node roundish in dorsal view, ending in a well-developed terminal spine. Pterostigma almost three times longer than broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,457,1250,1276]" box="[189,457,1250,1276]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,457,1250,1276]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,457,1250,1276]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1398,1296,1358]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
The general light brown colour is diagnostic, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boulard" authorityYear="1968" box="[747,812,1296,1322]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heimi">
<emphasis box="[747,812,1296,1322]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">heimi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[876,961,1297,1322]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[876,961,1297,1322]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">nigrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[971,1065,1297,1323]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
being black, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[1286,1398,1297,1322]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caneparii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1286,1398,1297,1322]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">caneparii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,280,1332,1358]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
having a mosaic of russet brown and black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,959,1397,1424]" box="[189,959,1397,1424]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
Other diagnostic characters with respect to 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[697,809,1398,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caneparii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[697,809,1398,1423]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">caneparii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[817,908,1398,1424]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,1447,1755]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
– the similarity of the width and height of the basal element of the suprahumeral horns (frontal view) (
<figureCitation box="[236,330,1482,1509]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[310,1289,325,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-12@13.[223,1365,266,1882]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology. Left suprahumeral horn and left supraocular callosity, frontal view. A. Hamma heimi Boulard, 1968. B. Hamma nigrum sp. nov. C. Hamma spinellii sp. nov. D. Hamma caneparii sp. nov. Figures are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745165/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
): in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[380,475,1482,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinellii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[380,475,1482,1508]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">spinellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[482,572,1483,1509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the w/h ratio is 1; in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[822,934,1483,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caneparii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[822,934,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">caneparii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[942,1032,1483,1509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the w/h ratio is 0.66;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,1447,1755]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
– caudal node of the posterior process half the width of the head in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[1014,1109,1518,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinellii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1014,1109,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">spinellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1116,1211,1518,1544]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; ⅔ the width in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[227,339,1554,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caneparii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[227,339,1554,1579]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">caneparii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[347,437,1553,1579]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(dorsal view);
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,1447,1755]" box="[189,1169,1588,1615]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
– anchor-like third node (
<figureCitation box="[503,593,1588,1615]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[252,1342,283,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-12@15.[239,1348,265,1881]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 5. Morphology. Pterostigma of right wing in dorsal view; third node of the posterior process in dorsal view; scutellum in lateral right view. A. Hamma heimi Boulard, 1968. B. Hamma nigrum sp. nov. C. Hamma spinellii sp. nov. D. Hamma caneparii sp. nov. Figures are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745167/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
) thinner than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[787,899,1589,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caneparii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[787,899,1589,1614]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">caneparii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[907,998,1589,1615]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(dorsal view);
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,1447,1755]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
– length of the posterior process clearly exceeding abdominal length in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[1031,1126,1623,1649]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinellii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1031,1126,1623,1649]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">spinellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1133,1225,1624,1650]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; not exceeding the abdominal terminalia in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[557,669,1659,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caneparii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[557,669,1659,1684]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">caneparii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[677,768,1659,1685]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(lateral view);
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,1447,1755]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
– pterostigma (
<figureCitation box="[382,473,1694,1721]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[252,1342,283,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-12@15.[239,1348,265,1881]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 5. Morphology. Pterostigma of right wing in dorsal view; third node of the posterior process in dorsal view; scutellum in lateral right view. A. Hamma heimi Boulard, 1968. B. Hamma nigrum sp. nov. C. Hamma spinellii sp. nov. D. Hamma caneparii sp. nov. Figures are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745167/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
) longer in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[605,700,1694,1720]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinellii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[605,700,1694,1720]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">spinellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[708,803,1694,1720]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: l/w ratio 
<quantity box="[923,991,1694,1720]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.636" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" unit="in" value="3.4">3.4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[999,1094,1694,1720]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinellii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[999,1094,1694,1720]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">spinellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1102,1197,1694,1720]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; 
<quantity box="[1210,1278,1694,1720]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.096" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" unit="in" value="2.4">2.4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[1286,1398,1695,1720]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caneparii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1286,1398,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">caneparii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[227,317,1729,1755]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1104,1794,1821]" box="[189,1104,1794,1821]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
Other diagnostic characters with respect to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boulard" authorityYear="1968" box="[697,762,1794,1820]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heimi">
<emphasis box="[697,762,1794,1820]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">heimi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[819,904,1795,1820]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[819,904,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">nigrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[911,1002,1795,1821]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
include:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,1845,2012]" box="[189,827,1845,1871]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
– upper margin of the head roughly square (
<figureCitation box="[720,813,1845,1871]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[310,1289,325,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-12@13.[223,1365,266,1882]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology. Left suprahumeral horn and left supraocular callosity, frontal view. A. Hamma heimi Boulard, 1968. B. Hamma nigrum sp. nov. C. Hamma spinellii sp. nov. D. Hamma caneparii sp. nov. Figures are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745165/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,1845,2012]" box="[189,629,1880,1906]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
– metopidium (
<figureCitation box="[385,475,1880,1906]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[310,1289,325,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-12@13.[223,1365,266,1882]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology. Left suprahumeral horn and left supraocular callosity, frontal view. A. Hamma heimi Boulard, 1968. B. Hamma nigrum sp. nov. C. Hamma spinellii sp. nov. D. Hamma caneparii sp. nov. Figures are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745165/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) tuberculate;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,1845,2012]" box="[189,1343,1915,1942]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
– suprahumeral horns (
<figureCitation box="[475,565,1915,1941]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[310,1289,325,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-12@13.[223,1365,266,1882]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology. Left suprahumeral horn and left supraocular callosity, frontal view. A. Hamma heimi Boulard, 1968. B. Hamma nigrum sp. nov. C. Hamma spinellii sp. nov. D. Hamma caneparii sp. nov. Figures are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745165/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) with a robust straight thorn, not curving upwards in frontal view;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,1845,2012]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
– anchor-like third node (
<figureCitation box="[502,591,1950,1977]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[252,1342,283,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-12@15.[239,1348,265,1881]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 5. Morphology. Pterostigma of right wing in dorsal view; third node of the posterior process in dorsal view; scutellum in lateral right view. A. Hamma heimi Boulard, 1968. B. Hamma nigrum sp. nov. C. Hamma spinellii sp. nov. D. Hamma caneparii sp. nov. Figures are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745167/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
) posteriorly prolonged (dorsal view); rhomboidal or roughly circular in 
<taxonomicName authority="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini, 2021" authorityName="Durante &amp; Loudit &amp; Susini" authorityYear="2021" box="[257,342,1986,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[257,342,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">nigrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[349,440,1986,2012]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boulard" authorityYear="1968" box="[496,561,1985,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Hamma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heimi">
<emphasis box="[496,561,1985,2011]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">heimi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
